# Laravel Architecture

We are using Laravel for our backend and application logic.

## Routing
- All web routes must be defined in `routes/web.php`.
- All API routes must be defined in `routes/api.php` and should return JSON responses.

## Controllers & Responses
<% if (options.frontend === 'blade') { %>
- We are using **Blade** templates. Controllers should return views using `return view('view-name');`.
<% } else if (options.frontend === 'livewire') { %>
- We are using **Livewire**. Prefer full-page Livewire components for dynamic pages rather than standard controllers.
<% } else if (options.frontend === 'inertia-vue') { %>
- We are using **Inertia.js with Vue**. Controllers must return Inertia responses using `return Inertia::render('Component/Name', [...]);`.
- Do NOT return Blade views unless it's the root `app.blade.php`.
<% } else if (options.frontend === 'inertia-react') { %>
- We are using **Inertia.js with React**. Controllers must return Inertia responses using `return Inertia::render('Component/Name', [...]);`.
- Do NOT return Blade views unless it's the root `app.blade.php`.
<% } else if (options.frontend === 'inertia-svelte') { %>
- We are using **Inertia.js with Svelte**. Controllers must return Inertia responses using `return Inertia::render('Component/Name', [...]);`.
- Do NOT return Blade views unless it's the root `app.blade.php`.
<% } else if (options.frontend === 'api-only') { %>
- We are building an **API Only** backend. All controllers must return JSON using `return response()->json([...]);` or Eloquent resources.
<% } else { %>
- Follow standard Laravel controller and routing practices.
<% } %>

## Models & Database
- Always use Eloquent ORM. Avoid raw SQL queries unless strictly necessary for performance.
- Use FormRequests for all validation logic to keep controllers clean.
